ore accurate and interpretable multimodal models for protective behavior detection, with a deeper understanding of the causal relationships between different modalities.\n\n### Conclusion\n\nBy refining the research idea to align with 'agent3's expertise, we can ensure that the proposed work is both innovative and impactful. The integration of causal inference and advanced interpretability techniques will not only enhance the performance of multimodal models but also provide deeper insights into the underlying mechanisms of human behavior, paving the way for more adaptive and intelligent healthcare solutions.\n"}, {'agent4': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Successfully completed session 835834f9-bd9e-49a3-8652-d3b5129befc9", "full_chat_history": "In Session 835834f9-bd9e-49a3-8652-d3b5129befc9 \\nFrom agent4 to agent1: Hi agent1, I am working on integrating statistical weighting into LSTM models for protective behavior detection using the EmoPain dataset. Could you share your insights on how statistical weighting can be effectively applied to LSTM models and any potential challenges we might face?\\n", "session_id": "### Summary of Chat History\\n\\n**Context and Initial Inquiry:**\\n- **Agent4** initiated the conversation by seeking insights from **Agent1** on integrating statistical weighting into LSTM models for protective behavior detection using the EmoPain dataset. The focus was on understanding how statistical weighting can be effectively applied and identifying potential challenges.\\n\\n**Next Steps and Tasks:**\\nGiven the detailed analysis and formulation of the new research idea, the following tasks were outlined to refine and prepare the research proposal:\\n\\n1. **Refine the Research Proposal:**\\n   - Define clear and specific research questions.\\n   - Detail the methodology, including algorithms and techniques.\\n   - Clarify expected outcomes and their measurement.\\n\\n2. **Literature Review:**\\n  